🧸 1. Virtual Threads (BIGGEST FEATURE)
👶 Problem (Old Java):

Imagine you have 1000 customers calling your shop 📞
You hire 1000 workers → expensive, slow, system crashes 😵

🆕 Solution:

Java 21 gives Virtual Threads = very tiny, lightweight workers

👉 One real worker can handle MANY calls

🧠 Simple idea:
Old thread = heavy elephant 🐘
Virtual thread = tiny ants 🐜 (thousands can work together)
💻 Use Case:
APIs (Spring Boot apps)
Microservices handling many users
Chat apps, booking systems

👉 You can now handle lakhs of users without crashing

🧸 2. Record Patterns (Smarter Data Checking)
👶 Problem:

You open a box 🎁 and check:

Is it a toy?
What color?
What size?

Too many steps 😩

🆕 Solution:

Java 21 lets you open + check in one step

💻 Example idea:

Instead of:

check type
cast object
get values

👉 You do everything in one clean line

🧠 Use Case:
Parsing API responses
Working with DTOs
Cleaner backend code
🧸 3. Pattern Matching for switch (Smarter Switch)
👶 Problem:

Old switch only works with simple things like numbers

🆕 Solution:

Now switch can understand:

objects
types
conditions
🧠 Example:

Instead of writing many if-else:

👉 You use one clean switch

💻 Use Case:
Request handling
Validation logic
Business rules
🧸 4. Sequenced Collections (Ordered Collections)
👶 Problem:

Sometimes you want:

first item
last item

But Java collections didn’t give easy methods 😓

🆕 Solution:

Now all collections support:

getFirst()
getLast()
reversed()
🧠 Use Case:
Recent transactions
Chat messages
Logs

👉 Easier and cleaner

🧸 5. String Templates (Better String Building)
👶 Problem:

Building strings is messy:

"Hello " + name + " your age is " + age

😵 Hard to read

🆕 Solution:

Java 21 introduces String Templates

👉 Cleaner like:

Hello {name}, age {age}
🧠 Use Case:
Logging
SQL queries
API messages
🧸 6. Scoped Values (Safe Data Sharing)
👶 Problem:

Threads sharing data = risky 😬
(data can change unexpectedly)

🆕 Solution:

Scoped Values = safe way to share data

👉 Only visible where needed

🧠 Use Case:
Security context
Request data in microservices
🧸 7. Foreign Function & Memory API (Advanced but Useful)
👶 Problem:

Calling C/C++ code is hard 😓

🆕 Solution:

Java 21 makes it easier to:

talk to native code
manage memory
🧠 Use Case:
High-performance apps
Integrating legacy systems
🧸 8. Unnamed Patterns & Variables (Less Boilerplate)
👶 Problem:

Sometimes you don’t care about a variable

But Java forces you to name it 😑

🆕 Solution:

Use _ to ignore

🧠 Example:
case User(_, age) -> ...

👉 Cleaner code

